Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, to sharpish turn. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Xenophon. From the same die as Athenian Agora SS13164
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (probably)
Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (possibly; trimming suggests is, but not surface condition)
